parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wiring Harness Failure and Insulation Degradation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to stalling, loss of brakes, and even fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Exposed copper wires
crumbling wire harness insulation
sparks when the harness is agitated
stalling at low speeds
loss of brakes
and fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Cable Failure Due to Improper Design
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch cable can cause the clutch pedal to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels stiff or hard to press
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling at Low Speeds with Loss of Brake Function
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the vehicle at low speeds, accompanied by a loss of brake function, can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at low speeds (e.g.
when stopping or turning)
the brakes fail to respond or are unresponsive
the vehicle is unable to slow down or stop
the driver may experience a sudden loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake pedal position sensor can cause the vehicle to stall or lose brake function, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at low speeds
the brakes fail to respond or are unresponsive
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle's anti-lock braking system (ABS) light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ETC system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the throttle pedal feels unresponsive
the engine RPM fluctuates or surges
the vehicle's "check engine" light illuminates on the dashboard.
